0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">Paul Halsall (2000) [1998]. Jerome S. Arkenberg, ed. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/eastasia/romchin1.html">"East Asian History Sourcebook: Chinese Accounts of Rome, Byzantium and the Middle East, c. 91 B.C.E. - 1643 C.E."</a>. <i>Fordham.edu</i>. <a href="/wiki/Fordham_University" title="Fordham University">Fordham University</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2016-09-14</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASong+dynasty&amp;rft.atitle=East+Asian+History+Sourcebook%3A+Chinese+Accounts+of+Rome%2C+Byzantium+and+the+Middle+East%2C+c.+91+B.C.E.+-+1643+C.E.&amp;rft.au=Paul+Halsall&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Fordham.edu&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fordham.edu%2Fhalsall%2Feastasia%2Fromchin1.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEMote199969-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEMote199969_16-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFMote1999">Mote 1999</a>, p.&#160;69.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEEbreyWalthallPalais2006154-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEEbreyWalthallPalais2006154_17-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFEbreyWalthallPalais2006">Ebrey, Walthall &amp; Palais 2006</a>, p.&#160;154.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEMote199970.E2.80.9371-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEMote199970.E2.80.9371_18-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFMote1999">Mote 1999</a>, pp.&#160;70\xe2\x80\x9371.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTESivin19958-19"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTESivin19958_19-0"